Case 3-Asia-Indus-Figurine-Female-Solid Terra Cotta-3300-1300 BCE

Asia-Indus-Figurine Female-Solid Terra Cotta-3300-1300 BCE

Case no.: 3

Accession Number:

Formal Label: Asia-Indus-Figurine Female-Solid Terra Cotta-3300-1300 BCE

Display Description:

This Indus-Female Figurine has a Solid Terra Cotta core. She resembles many of the pillar figurines except or the solid core. She holds a torch in her right hand and her left arm is situated under her left breast. The torch signifies she is a priestess leading others in a nocturnal ceremony.
